fields and may be sponsored in part by student organizations or departments informal yet still professional unlike most job fairs stanford's career fairs are usually casual even the employers tend to dress down although informal do remember that these are potential employers and distasteful dress and decorum is not appropriate when getting dressed for the event keep in mind the industry and type of position you desire no cost and pre advertised lists stanford's career development center sponsored career fairs are free to job seekers lists of participating employers are made available prior to the event on the cdc web page via your cardinal careers account the employer information includes type of position being sought ie technical vs non technical full time part time or internship how students found jobs up on campus recruiting groups career development center printer friendly version calendar schedule an appointment graphic calendar pages schedule an appointment with a career counselor quick links calendar career fair schedule career planning handbook career library vault guided career path facebook linkedin what is the cdc copyright 2011 stanford university terms of use copyright complaints report a problem with this site
